title: Manchester United news: Wayne Rooney, Michael Carrick and Phil Jones miss training | Metro News
text:
Mark Brus for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 15 Feb 2017 12:17 pm Jose Mourinho has a potential Europa League headache (Picture: Getty) 
Manchester United were without three key players in training today as they prepare to face Saint-Etienne in the Europa League on Thursday night. ‘How can Gibbs be captain?!’ Man Utd legend Roy Keane TEARS into Arsenal flops 
The Red Devils welcome the Ligue 1 outfit to Old Trafford tomorrow evening, but have already been dealt a major potential blow as Wayne Rooney, Michael Carrick and Phil Jones could be set to miss out. 
Carrick and Jones have been particularly impressive of late after being given more of a role by manager Jose Mourinho, while the experience of Rooney has served the club well in the Europa League this season. Some key players missed United training (Picture: Getty) 
However, the Manchester Evening News suggests United may have to cope without them against Saint-Etienne, with Jones still recovering from a bruised foot, though it is not clear why Rooney and Carrick could be unavailable. 
Marcos Rojo is expected to play after returning to training, having missed the game against Watford after limping off in the win over Leicester City.
